	<h1>GIR - Greens in regulation</h1>
	<p>For greens in regulation (GIR) we need to know whether you hit the green or not, and where the ball came to a stop.</p>
	<p>&nbsp;</p>
	<h2>Entering your data</h2>
	<div class="floatEnder"></div>	
	<div style="float: left; width: 101px; margin-right: 10px;">
		<p><img class="imgBorder" src="/tracker/wl/lovegolf/images/im-help-gir-missed.gif" height="47" width="99" alt="GIR missed" /></p>
	</div>
	<div style="float: right; width: 410px;">
		<p>If you <strong>failed</strong> to hit the green, leave the checkbox <strong>unticked</strong>. Then choose where the ball came to a stop. Your options are:</p>
		<ul>
			<li><strong>Left</strong> - Off the green to the left. This includes shots that went out of bounds.</li>
			<li><strong>Right</strong> - Off the green to the Right. This includes shots that went out of bounds.</li>
			<li><strong>Long</strong> - Too long and past the green.</li>
			<li><strong>Short</strong> - Short of the green.</li>
		</ul>
	</div>
	<div class="floatEnder"></div>
	<p>&nbsp;</p>
	<div style="float: left; width: 101px; margin-right: 10px;">
		<p><img class="imgBorder" src="/tracker/wl/lovegolf/images/im-help-gir-hit.gif" height="47" width="99" alt="GIR hit" /></p>
	</div>
	<div style="float: right; width: 410px;">
		<p>If you <strong>succeeded</strong> in hitting the green, click the checkbox to tick it. Then choose where the ball came to a stop <strong>in relation to the pin</strong>, not the centre of the green. Your options are:</p>
		<ul>
			<li><strong>Pin</strong> - On the green and within 10 feet of the pin in any direction.</li>
			<li><strong>Left</strong> - On the green to the left of the pin.</li>
			<li><strong>Right</strong> - On the green to the right of the pin.</li>
			<li><strong>Long</strong> - On the green and past the pin.</li>
			<li><strong>Short</strong> - On the green and short of the pin.</li>
		</ul>
	</div>
	<div class="floatEnder"></div>
	
</div>